e, Digitization, and Dalí's Memory," which further explores language’s role in preserving and enhancing our humanity in the digital age.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aLanguage Arts & Linguistics. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aMedia Studies.  aHermeneutics, digitization, cognition, interpretation, language, reception of literary, technological transformation, communication.1 aZlatic, Thomas D., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 avan den Berg, Sara, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066587108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2018 Englishz978311060407808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2018z9783110603170oZDB-23-DSP40uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150171450440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501714504423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501714504/original  a978-3-11-060407-8  EBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-066587-1  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DSPb2018